[[Image:Bumba-meu-boi.jpg|right|thumb|Big Bumba-meu-boi in the [[Paço Alfândega]] cultural center and mall, [[Recife]]]]
'''Boi''' is a style of Central [[Amazon Rainforest|Amazonian]] [[folk music]] now moving into the mainstream in [[Brazil]]. It is a combination of traditional Amazonian rhythms with African and European influence. The genre was made known throughout Brazil after Amazonian group [[Carrapicho]]'s hit "[[Tic Tic Tac]]".
