'''David Kaye''' (born '''David Friedman''') is a professional [[Magic (illusion)|magician]] and author. He performs under the [[stage name]] '''Silly Billy'''.

== Bibliography ==
He authored a long-running column for [[Magic (magazine)|''Magic'' magazine]] entitled, "Turn it around: Magic for the family audience."<ref>{{cite journal | title=Turn it around | author=Kaye, David | journal=Magic |date=April 2007 | volume=16 | issue=8 | pages=92–93}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Kaye is the son of Arnold and Elaine Friedman. He is the oldest of their three sons. Kaye's younger brothers are Seth and Jesse.<ref name="LIP">{{cite news |date=June 12, 2003 |title=Brother's Keeper |url=http://archive.longislandpress.com/2003/06/12/brothers-keeper/ |newspaper=Long Island Press  }}</ref> He grew up in [[Flushing, Queens]], and then moved to [[Great Neck, New York|Great Neck]], [[Long Island]], with his family when he was a teenager.<ref name="coping">{{cite news |date=June 8, 2003 |title=COPING; A Clown's Sad Tale, And the Solace Of a Silly Hat |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/06/08/nyregion/coping-a-clown-s-sad-tale-and-the-solace-of-a-silly-hat.html |newspaper=The New York Times }}</ref>

Kaye adopted his current surname in the 1990s.<ref name="timeout">{{cite news |date=March 1, 2005 |title=Man about clown: New York's best-known party clown talks about magic, psychology and life after Capturing the Friedmans |url=https://www.timeout.com/new-york-kids/things-to-do/man-about-clown |newspaper=Time Out New York }}</ref> He says he registered with the union for television performers with the surname Kaye to differentiate himself from the 27 David Friedmans already in the union.<ref name="coping"/>

