{{Refimprove|date=September 2008}}

'''Shallow diving''' is an [[extreme sport]], whereby enthusiasts attempt to [[Diving (sport)|dive]] from the greatest height into the shallowest depth of water, without sustaining injury. It is typically associated with travelling circuses along with the [[Strongman (strength athlete)|strongman]], [[performing animals]], [[clown]]s and other such attractions.

==Technique==
Divers aim to hit the water horizontally in a manner akin to the [[Belly flop]]. This spreads the impact over the greatest surface area, and achieves the longest time decelerating, before hitting the bottom of the container where the water is held.

==World record==
* [[Professor Splash]] (ne. Darren Taylor) successfully dove from {{convert|11.52|m|ft|disp=flip|abbr=out}} into a paddling pool of depth {{convert|30|cm|ft|disp=flip|abbr=out|sigfig=1}} breaking his record for a successive 20th time.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thorne|first=Dan|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/news/60at60/2015/8/2005-highest-shallow-dive-392864 |title=w005:Highest Shallow Dive|publisher=Guinness World Records|website=guinnessworldrecords.com |date=2015-08-18 |accessdate=2017-06-25}}</ref>
* [[Roy Fransen]] successfully dove from {{convert|110|ft|m|abbr=out|sigfig=3}} into {{convert|8|ft|m|abbr=out|sigfig=2}} of water.

